This paper deals with the transmission of confidential messages over a multiple-access channel corrupted by fading and additive white Gaussian noise. It involves the study of secrecy capacity regions and power allocation functions, which are typical topics in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of fading gain coefficients and channel state information also suggests a connection to wireless communication (cs.MM) and networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the consideration of eavesdropping and secrecy also relates to the field of security and privacy (cs.SI).
